{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "vexstatement", "group": "array", "context": "all"}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["foreach"], "extent": [0, 12]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Loops over the items in an array, with optional enumeration."], "extent": [62, 130]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The length of the array is determined before the first iteration, so if the array is changed during the foreach this will not be reflected in the number of iterations."], "extent": [130, 300]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Simple form"], "extent": [300, 318], "body": [{"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nforeach ([element_type] value; array) {\n\n}\n"], "extent": [318, 376]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This loops over the members of ", {"type": "var", "text": ["array"]}, ". For each iteration, it ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["copies"]}, "\nthe current member to ", {"type": "var", "text": ["value"]}, " and then executes ", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, ". For example:"], "extent": [376, 530]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nint an_array[] = {1, 2}\nforeach (int num; an_array) {\n    printf(\"%d\", num);\n}\n"], "extent": [530, 623]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Enumerated form"], "extent": [623, 647], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The second form lets you specify an enumeration variable:"], "extent": [647, 707]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nforeach (index, value; array) statement;\nforeach (int index; element_type value; array) statement;\n"], "extent": [707, 820]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For each iteration, this form assigns the current ", {"type": "em", "text": ["position"]}, " in the array\nto ", {"type": "var", "text": ["index"]}, ", ", {"type": "strong", "text": ["copies"]}, " the current member to ", {"type": "var", "text": ["value"]}, ", and executes\n", {"type": "var", "text": ["statement"]}, ". For example:"], "extent": [820, 993]}, {"lang": "vex", "type": "pre", "indent": 0, "text": ["\nstring days[] = { \"Mon\", \"Tue\", \"Wed\", \"Thu\", \"Fri\" }\nforeach (int i; string name; days) {\n    printf(\"Day number %d is %s\", i, name);\n}\n"], "extent": [993, 1144]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This is similar to the common Python idiom ", {"type": "code", "text": ["for i, x in enumerate(xs):"]}, "."], "extent": [1144, 1220]}]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1220, 1229], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "/vex/arrays", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/vex/arrays"}], "extent": [1229, 1247]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["foreach"], "summary": ["Loops over the items in an array, with optional enumeration."]}